description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, forward-thinking Pharmacist to join our experienced and friendly team dedicated to providing an advanced clinical Oncology/Haematology service and supply of aseptic products to the Trust. As well as being one of our Specialist Oncology Pharmacists, the post holder will also be the Specialist Biologics Pharmacist, developing the current pharmacy service to patients requiring biologic therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will suit candidates with previous hospital experience, including experience within aseptics and oncology considering a move into a more specialist pharmacist role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have recently completed a Pharmacy Transformation Programme to include refurbishment of the department and adoption of the latest technology to include a Chemotherapy EPMA system, automated robotic and controlled drug dispensing and e-Rostering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Edward Hawley-Jones Job title: Lead Pharmacist Oncology, Haematology &amp; Clinical Trials&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Edward.Hawley-Jones@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01234 355122 ext 6230&lt;/p&gt;
